text: Trent Alexander Boult (born 22 July 1989 in Rotorua) was a New Zealand cricketer who played 78 tests, 99 one-day internationals and 55 twenty20 internationals from 2011 to 2022. He is the younger brother of Jono Boult. He grew up in ÅŒhope and Tauranga and is of Maori descent. He has taken two One- day Internationals hat-tricks in 2018 and 2019. ==Other websites== * * Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand cricketers Category:Sportspeople from North Island
